description: Try our easy to follow Moroccan Spiced Chicken  recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Moroccan Spiced Chicken Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 jar MasterFoods Moroccan Style Spice Paste

recipeInstructions.text: Put the chicken breasts into a bowl and smother with all the spice paste
Heat an oven proof fry pan over a medium heat and fry the chicken 3-4 minutes until golden. Turn over, then cook in the oven for 10-12 minutes until cooked and sticky.
Boil the kettle with the 4 cups of water. Add to couscous. Let sit for 10 minutes. Stir in cranberries, almonds, olives and parsley (lemon juice option).
Blend all tahini mint sauce ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Assemble the couscous, chicken and add on the tahini mint sauce
